stream
BT /F2 16 Tf 72.0 720.0 Td (Emergency Procurement Policy) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 72.0 692.0 Td (Document ID: POL-PROC-003   |   Type: POLICY   |   Effective: 2024-01-01) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 72.0 662.0 Td (EMERGENCY PROCUREMENT POLICY) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 646.0 Td (Document ID: POL-PROC-003) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 630.0 Td (Version: 1.6) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 614.0 Td (Effective Date: 2024-01-01) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 598.0 Td (Owner: VP Supply Chain) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 72.0 574.0 Td (1. PURPOSE) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 558.0 Td (This policy defines the conditions under which emergency procurement procedures) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 542.0 Td (may be invoked, the approval authority in emergency situations, and the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 526.0 Td (documentation requirements for post-event audit.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 72.0 502.0 Td (2. DEFINITION OF EMERGENCY) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 486.0 Td (An emergency procurement situation exists when:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 470.0 Td (\(a\) On-hand inventory has fallen to zero or is critically below safety stock,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 454.0 Td (creating an imminent production or operational stoppage; or) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 438.0 Td (\(b\) A supplier has failed to deliver against an existing purchase order within) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 422.0 Td (the contracted lead time and no buffer stock exists; or) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 406.0 Td (\(c\) A force-majeure event has disrupted standard supply channels.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 382.0 Td (For the purposes of the automated procurement system, a requisition is classified) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 366.0 Td (as critical urgency when on-hand quantity is more than twice the safety stock) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 350.0 Td (level below the required quantity.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 72.0 326.0 Td (3. APPROVAL AUTHORITY IN EMERGENCIES) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 72.0 302.0 Td (3.1 Critical Urgency Requisitions Below $5,000) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 286.0 Td (Critical urgency purchase requisitions with an estimated cost below $5,000 placed) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 270.0 Td (against a preferred vendor are auto-approved under POL-PROC-001 and do not) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 254.0 Td (require additional emergency authorisation.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 72.0 230.0 Td (3.2 Critical Urgency Requisitions $5,000 \20023 $25,000) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 214.0 Td (Critical urgency purchase requisitions with an estimated cost between $5,000 and) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 198.0 Td ($25,000 require manager approval. The manager must respond within 4 business) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 182.0 Td (hours of the approval request being raised. Failure to respond within this window) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 166.0 Td (escalates automatically to the VP Supply Chain.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 72.0 142.0 Td (3.3 Critical Urgency Requisitions Above $25,000) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 126.0 Td (Even in emergency situations, purchase requisitions exceeding $25,000 must be) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 110.0 Td (approved by an executive \(VP Supply Chain or above\). The automated system will) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 94.0 Td (deny such requisitions and route them to the executive approval queue. Verbal) Tj ET
endstream
